description.narrative: (Ethiopia): .Transform: Primary Health Care (PHC) strives to prevent child and maternal deaths and support Ethiopia's Health Sector Transformation Plan with a focus on family planning, maternal, newborn and child health, obstetric fistula, adolescent and youth health and nutrition in the five agrarian regions: Amhara, Oromia, Tigray, Sidama and SNNP. Through targeted technical assistance that advances self-reliance in the health sector, the activity will: 1) Strengthen management and performance of health systems at the PHC level; 2) Increase sustainable service quality across the PHC unit's continuum of care; 3) Improve household and community health practices and health-seeking behavior; and 4) Enhance program learning to impact policy and programming. Districts are eligible for performance improvement sub-grants. ..Through technical assistance and training, this activity supports regional and sub-regional management structures to build leadership and management competencies to improve health system performance and health service quality. It supports strategic planning and ability to effectively use data in real time to meet communities' health needs, including outbreak response. These skills are vital as Ethiopia seeks to optimize limited resources in the face of immense needs and recurrent health shocks, and to build a strong, competent health workforce able to better plan, fund and manage their own continued progress toward a higher standard of health and resilient health systems. Interventions target lower performing districts and under-served populations where USAID resources can have the greatest impact to prevent child and maternal deaths, a Mission priority. The activity also supports public health emergency response, including COVID 19, to ensure that critical PHC services continue even during outbreaks, thus ensuring continuity of essential health services to prevent maternal and child deaths. ..
